    "actor_description": "I stop reaching for the wheel. My attention sinks and stays—caught, held, almost tenderly restrained. The world narrows to one thread, and the rest of me goes quiet around it. I can still feel my body, but it’s distant, obedient—breathing slower, muscles forgetting their usual fidget. Time feels thicker here.",
    "description_text": "{actor} goes unusually still, gaze fixed as if something has hooked their attention and won’t let go. Their blinking slows; their posture softens into a held pause. It’s not sleepiness—it’s capture, a quiet surrender of movement to focus.",
